	<h3 class='head3'>Being good to yourself</h3>
	<p class='para'>Sometimes older adults feel lonely, sad, low, or stressed because of life changes, loss of loved ones, health problems, caring for other family members, or financial issues. Being good to yourself may help you improve your lifestyle habits, your “get up and go,” and your ability to cope with the demands of daily living.</p>
	<p class='para'>Here are some ideas for being good to yourself</p>
	<ul class='ulist'>
	<li class='list'>Stay in touch with family, friends, or former coworkers to stay engaged and to keep your spirits up.</li>
	<li class='list'>See your health care professional regularly and share any concerns.</li>
	<li class='list'>Get enough sleep.</li>
	<li class='list'>If you are retired, pursue a new hobby or volunteer to help keep you active and social.</li>
	<li class='list'>Join a walking group or another social group.</li>
	<li class='list'>Surround yourself with people you enjoy.</li>
	</ul>
